<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>NYC · Family Trip · June 2026</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root { --ink:#1a1814;--cream:#f5f0e8;--gold:#b8912a;--gold-light:#d4a843;--rust:#8b3a2f;--sage:#4a5c4e;--stone:#9c9488;--white:#fdfbf7;--day1:#8b3a2f;--day2:#4a5c4e;--day3:#2c4a6e;--day4:#6b3d6b;--day5:#8b6914; }
  *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box;}
  body{font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;background:var(--cream);color:var(--ink);font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;}
  .hero{background:var(--ink);color:var(--cream);min-height:340px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;text-align:center;padding:60px 24px 50px;position:relative;overflow:hidden;}
  .hero::before{content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;background:radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 50% at 20% 80%,rgba(184,145,42,.15) 0%,transparent 60%),radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 40% at 80% 20%,rgba(139,58,47,.12) 0%,transparent 60%);}
  .hero-eyebrow{font-size:11px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:4px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gold-light);margin-bottom:18px;position:relative;}
  .hero h1{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:clamp(38px,8vw,72px);font-weight:400;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:20px;position:relative;}
  .hero h1 em{font-style:italic;color:var(--gold-light);}
  .hero-sub{font-size:14px;color:rgba(245,240,232,.65);letter-spacing:1px;position:relative;}
  .hero-divider{width:40px;height:1px;background:var(--gold);margin:22px auto;position:relative;}
  .hero-tags{display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;margin-top:26px;position:relative;}
  .hero-tag{border:1px solid rgba(184,145,42,.4);color:rgba(245,240,232,.7);padding:5px 14px;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.5px;text-transform:uppercase;}
  .tabs-wrapper{position:sticky;top:0;z-index:100;background:var(--ink);border-bottom:1px solid rgba(184,145,42,.25);}
  .tabs{display:flex;overflow-x:auto;scrollbar-width:none;max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;}
  .tabs::-webkit-scrollbar{display:none;}
  .tab{flex-shrink:0;padding:14px 20px;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(245,240,232,.45);cursor:pointer;border-bottom:2px solid transparent;transition:all .2s;white-space:nowrap;background:none;border-left:none;border-right:none;border-top:none;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-weight:500;}
  .tab:hover{color:rgba(245,240,232,.75);}
  .tab.active{color:var(--gold-light);border-bottom-color:var(--gold);}
  .section{display:none;max-width:960px;margin:0 auto;padding:48px 20px 80px;}
  .section.active{display:block;}
  .section-header{margin-bottom:40px;padding-bottom:20px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(26,24,20,.12);}
  .section-header h2{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:32px;font-weight:400;margin-bottom:8px;}
  .section-header p{color:var(--stone);font-size:14px;}
  .day-block{margin-bottom:52px;}
  .day-header{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:18px;margin-bottom:24px;}
  .day-badge{width:52px;height:52px;border-radius:50%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;color:white;font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;flex-direction:column;line-height:1.2;}
  .day-badge span{font-size:9px;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:1px;text-transform:uppercase;}
  .day-title{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:400;}
  .day-zone{font-size:12px;color:var(--stone);letter-spacing:1.5px;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:3px;}
  .timeline{position:relative;padding-left:28px;}
  .timeline::before{content:'';position:absolute;left:8px;top:6px;bottom:6px;width:1px;background:rgba(26,24,20,.1);}
  .event{position:relative;margin-bottom:22px;padding:18px 20px;background:var(--white);border-left:3px solid #ddd;}
  .event::before{content:'';position:absolute;left:-34px;top:22px;width:9px;height:9px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--stone);border:2px solid var(--cream);}
  .event.eat{border-left-color:var(--gold);}
  .event.eat::before{background:var(--gold);}
  .event.attraction{border-left-color:var(--sage);}
  .event.attraction::before{background:var(--sage);}
  .event.tip{border-left-color:#9c8866;background:#faf7f0;}
  .event.mussel{border-left-color:#2c6e8a;}
  .event.mussel::before{background:#2c6e8a;}
  .event-time{font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--stone);margin-bottom:4px;}
  .event-title{font-size:15px;font-weight:500;margin-bottom:4px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;flex-wrap:wrap;}
  .badge{font-size:9px;padding:2px 8px;letter-spacing:1px;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:500;border-radius:2px;}
  .badge-reserve{background:#fce8e4;color:var(--rust);}
  .badge-kids{background:#e8f0e8;color:var(--sage);}
  .badge-photo{background:#fdf4e0;color:#8b6914;}
  .badge-local{background:#e4eef2;color:#2c6e8a;}
  .badge-iconic{background:#f0e8f4;color:#6b3d6b;}
  .badge-free{background:#f0ece8;color:#5c5248;}
  .badge-mussel{background:#e0f0f8;color:#2c6e8a;font-weight:700;}
  .event-desc{font-size:13.5px;color:#3a3630;line-height:1.6;}
  .event-cost{font-size:12px;color:var(--stone);margin-top:6px;}
  .event-cost strong{color:var(--gold);}
  .event-duration{font-size:11px;color:#b0a898;margin-top:3px;}
  .info-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(280px,1fr));gap:20px;margin-bottom:36px;}
  .info-card{background:var(--white);padding:24px;border-top:3px solid var(--gold);}
  .info-card h3{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:17px;margin-bottom:14px;font-weight:400;}
  .info-card ul{list-style:none;}
  .info-card ul li{padding:7px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(26,24,20,.06);font-size:13.5px;display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:flex-start;}
  .info-card ul li:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
  .info-card .icon{flex-shrink:0;font-size:14px;margin-top:1px;}
  .budget-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:20px 0;}
  .budget-table th{text-align:left;padding:10px 14px;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--stone);border-bottom:1px solid rgba(26,24,20,.12);font-weight:400;}
  .budget-table td{padding:11px 14px;font-size:13.5px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(26,24,20,.06);}
  .budget-table .amount{text-align:right;font-weight:500;color:var(--ink);}
  .budget-table .total td{background:var(--ink);color:var(--cream);}
  .budget-table .total .amount{color:var(--gold-light);}
  .top10-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:16px;}
  .top10-item{background:var(--white);padding:22px;display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:flex-start;}
  .top10-num{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:28px;color:rgba(26,24,20,.1);line-height:1;flex-shrink:0;width:36px;}
  .top10-content h4{font-size:14px;font-weight:500;margin-bottom:4px;}
  .top10-content p{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--stone);line-height:1.5;}
  .checklist{list-style:none;}
  .checklist li{display:flex;gap:12px;padding:12px 0;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(26,24,20,.07);font-size:13.5px;align-items:flex-start;}
  .checklist li:last-child{border-bottom:none;}
  .checklist .check-icon{width:20px;height:20px;border:1.5px solid var(--gold);border-radius:3px;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:11px;color:var(--gold);}
  .checklist .urgency{font-size:11px;color:var(--rust);font-weight:500;}
  .alert{padding:16px 20px;margin:20px 0;border-left:3px solid var(--rust);background:#fef8f7;font-size:13.5px;}
  .alert strong{color:var(--rust);}
  .alert-gold{border-left-color:var(--gold);background:#fdf9f0;}
  .alert-gold strong{color:#8b6914;}
  .alert-sage{border-left-color:var(--sage);background:#f0f4f0;}
  .alert-sage strong{color:var(--sage);}
  .alert-blue{border-left-color:#2c6e8a;background:#f0f6fa;}
  .alert-blue strong{color:#2c6e8a;}
  .section-divider{text-align:center;margin:36px 0;position:relative;}
  .section-divider::before{content:'';position:absolute;left:0;right:0;top:50%;height:1px;background:rgba(26,24,20,.1);}
  .section-divider span{position:relative;background:var(--cream);padding:0 16px;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:3px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--stone);}
  .rain-banner{background:var(--day3);color:white;padding:20px 24px;margin-bottom:28px;display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:center;}
  .rain-icon{font-size:28px;}
  .rain-banner h3{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:400;}
  .rain-banner p{font-size:13px;opacity:.75;margin-top:2px;}
  .restaurant-feature{background:var(--ink);color:var(--cream);padding:24px 28px;margin:28px 0;border-left:4px solid #2c6e8a;}
  .restaurant-feature h3{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:400;color:var(--gold-light);margin-bottom:8px;}
  .restaurant-feature p{font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.7;opacity:.85;}
  footer{background:var(--ink);color:rgba(245,240,232,.45);text-align:center;padding:30px 20px;font-size:12px;letter-spacing:1px;}
  footer em{color:var(--gold-light);font-style:normal;}
  @media(max-width:600px){.section{padding:32px 16px 60px;}.info-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}.top10-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}.hero h1{font-size:36px;}}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-eyebrow">Luxury Family Concierge · June 2026</div>
  <h1>New York City<br><em>as a family</em></h1>
  <div class="hero-divider"></div>
  <div class="hero-sub">Jun 10–14 · Empire Hotel, Upper West Side · JetBlue B6 904 · SJU → JFK T5 · Arrives 2:01 PM</div>
  <div class="hero-tags">
    <span class="hero-tag">2 kids · ages 6 &amp; 7</span>
    <span class="hero-tag">Full family · 4 people</span>
    <span class="hero-tag">5 curated days</span>
    <span class="hero-tag">Local, not tourist</span>
    <span class="hero-tag">🦪 Mussel night included</span>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="tabs-wrapper">
  <div class="tabs">
    <button class="tab active" onclick="showTab('itinerary')">Itinerary</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('rain')">☁️ Rain Plan</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('restaurants')">🍽️ Restaurants</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('reservations')">Reservations</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('budget')">Budget</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('top10')">Top 10</button>
    <button class="tab" onclick="showTab('tips')">Pro Tips</button>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ITINERARY -->
<div id="itinerary" class="section active">
  <div class="section-header">
    <h2>Day by Day Itinerary</h2>
    <p>Curated to maximize experiences · minimize transit · stay local · include rest</p>
  </div>
  <div class="alert alert-gold">
    <strong>📍 Your base advantage:</strong> Empire Hotel is one block from Central Park and across from Lincoln Center. The American Museum of Natural History is a 7-minute walk. You barely need to move — the neighborhood does the work.
  </div>
  <div class="alert alert-blue">
    <strong>🧭 The philosophy:</strong> You're not here to check boxes. You're here to show your kids what a real city feels like — its rhythm, its food, its scale. Every restaurant in this guide is where New Yorkers actually eat.
  </div>

  <!-- DAY 1 -->
  <div class="day-block">
    <div class="day-header">
      <div class="day-badge" style="background:var(--day1);"><span>Day</span>1</div>
      <div>
        <div class="day-title">Arrival &amp; The Neighborhood</div>
        <div class="day-zone">📍 Wednesday Jun 10 · Upper West Side · Central Park</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">2:01 PM · JFK Terminal 5</div>
        <div class="event-title">🛬 Land · Baggage · Uber XL to hotel</div>
        <div class="event-desc">JetBlue T5 baggage claim is fast. Request an Uber XL while waiting for bags — with 4 people and luggage it's worth it. Arrive at the hotel around 3:30–3:45 PM depending on traffic.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 Uber XL JFK → Hotel: ~$75–95</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">3:30 – 4:15 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🏨 Check-in · Unpack · Decompress</div>
        <div class="event-desc">Don't rush this. Let the kids stretch. Ask the front desk for a high-floor room with a view — and mention you're traveling with young children. Upgrades happen at check-in, not over the phone. Also ask for late checkout on Day 5 while you're at it.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">4:30 – 6:15 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🌳 Central Park — First walk <span class="badge badge-kids">Kids love it</span> <span class="badge badge-photo">📸 Photo stop</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">Enter at Columbus Circle (1 block from the hotel). Today's route is gentle: walk to <strong>Strawberry Fields</strong> (the Lennon memorial mosaic), then down to <strong>Bethesda Fountain</strong> — the most photographed spot in the park, and stunning with late afternoon light. The <strong>Central Park Carousel</strong> is nearby if the kids have energy. June light in the park lasts until 8:30 PM. No schedule, no hurry.</div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ ~1.5 hrs at your pace</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 Free · Carousel: $4/person</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">7:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🌿 DINNER: Tavern on the Green <span class="badge badge-iconic">Iconic NYC</span> <span class="badge badge-photo">📸 Photo stop</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">Walk here directly from the park — the restaurant is literally inside Central Park. The garden terrace with string lights at dusk on a June evening is one of the most beautiful dinner settings in the city. American menu with solid kids options. This is the perfect "first night in New York" dinner — you'll feel it the moment you sit down.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$110–140 family · Reserve in advance</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event tip">
        <div class="event-title">💡 9 PM — Back to the hotel, everyone sleeps</div>
        <div class="event-desc">5-minute walk back. Travel day + first afternoon in the city is enough. The kids need rest for Day 2 — the biggest day of the trip for them. Don't add anything else tonight.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- DAY 2 -->
  <div class="day-block">
    <div class="day-header">
      <div class="day-badge" style="background:var(--day2);"><span>Day</span>2</div>
      <div>
        <div class="day-title">The Met + Dinosaurs — Big Museum Day</div>
        <div class="day-zone">📍 Thursday Jun 11 · Upper East Side · The Met · AMNH · Upper West Side</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">8:30 AM</div>
        <div class="event-title">☕ BREAKFAST: Zabar's <span class="badge badge-local">UWS institution since 1934</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">The most beloved deli on the Upper West Side — and one of the most New York things you can do. Bagels with lox, cream cheese, smoked fish, coffee. Get it and eat standing or take it back to the hotel. This is how the neighborhood eats. On Amsterdam Ave, 8 min from the hotel.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$35–50 family</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">10:00 AM – 12:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🎨 The Metropolitan Museum of Art <span class="badge badge-iconic">One of the world's greatest museums</span> <span class="badge badge-kids">Knights + mummies</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">
          Take the subway from Columbus Circle to 86th St (4, 5, or 6 line) — 10 minutes. The Met is on Fifth Avenue, facing Central Park.<br><br>
          <strong>Focused route for kids aged 6–7 (2.5 hours):</strong><br>
          1. <strong>Arms &amp; Armor</strong> (first floor) → Full suits of armor on horseback, European knights vs. Japanese samurai. The room that makes kids go completely quiet with awe.<br>
          2. <strong>Egyptian Wing + Temple of Dendur</strong> → A 2,000-year-old Egyptian temple reconstructed inside the museum, lit by a giant glass wall. Mummies, hieroglyphs, the real thing.<br>
          3. <strong>Rooftop Garden</strong> (weather permitting) → Panoramic views of Central Park and the Manhattan skyline from the 5th floor. One of the best views in the city, included with admission.<br><br>
          <strong>Tip:</strong> Grab the free family activity booklets at the information desk — they turn the visit into a scavenger hunt for kids. Skip the paintings for now — save those for when the kids are older.<br><br>
          <strong>Cost note:</strong> Children under 12 always free. Adults $30 (fixed mandatory fee for visitors from Puerto Rico).
        </div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ 2.5 hours — focused, not exhaustive</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 $30/adult · Kids under 12 free · Adults only ~$60 total</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">12:45 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🍔 LUNCH: J.G. Melon <span class="badge badge-local">NYC classic since 1972</span> <span class="badge badge-iconic">Cash only</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">5-minute walk from the Met along Third Avenue. J.G. Melon has been on this corner since 1972 — green and white checked tablecloths, dark wood bar, a multigenerational saloon that New Yorkers bring their kids to. The burger is serious. The cottage fries are legendary. <strong>Cash only — bring cash.</strong> No reservations, arrive by 12:45 PM before the line builds.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$55–70 family · Cash only</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">2:30 – 5:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🦕 American Museum of Natural History — Dinosaurs focused <span class="badge badge-reserve">⭐ Book ahead</span> <span class="badge badge-kids">Trip highlight</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">
          Walk or Uber from J.G. Melon to the AMNH (15 min walk or 5 min Uber). Afternoon visit — focused and efficient. The kids have already done the Met this morning so energy matters. Go straight for the dinosaurs.<br><br>
          <strong>Afternoon route — dinosaurs first, everything else optional:</strong><br>
          1. Hall of Saurischian Dinosaurs → T-Rex, Allosaurus, Velociraptor<br>
          2. Hall of Ornithischian Dinosaurs → Triceratops, Stegosaurus<br>
          3. <strong>The Titanosaur</strong> — 122 feet long, neck touching the ceiling. This is the moment of the day.<br>
          4. Milstein Hall of Ocean Life → the 94-foot blue whale, if they still have energy<br><br>
          <strong>Skip the Space Show today</strong> — save it for a rain day. Two museums in one day is already a full achievement. Get in, see the dinosaurs, leave happy.
        </div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ 2.5 hours — dinosaurs only, no rushing</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$25 adults / $14 kids · Total family ~$78 (no add-ons today)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event">
        <div class="event-time">5:30 – 7:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🛌 Rest at the hotel — non-negotiable</div>
        <div class="event-desc">Two museums in one day is ambitious. Walk back to the hotel (7 min from AMNH) and build in real downtime. This is the heaviest day of the trip mentally — the kids need to decompress and so do you. Empire rooftop for the adults, room for the kids.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">7:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🌮 DINNER: Gabriela's Restaurant &amp; Tequila Bar <span class="badge badge-local">UWS neighborhood favorite</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">Mexican restaurant that's been a UWS staple for years. Energetic, family-friendly, great margaritas for the adults, solid food the kids will love. 5-minute walk from the hotel. No travel required — exactly what you need after a big day.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$70–90 family</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- DAY 3 -->
  <div class="day-block">
    <div class="day-header">
      <div class="day-badge" style="background:var(--day3);"><span>Day</span>3</div>
      <div>
        <div class="day-title">Midtown Done Right</div>
        <div class="day-zone">📍 Friday Jun 12 · Grand Central · SUMMIT One Vanderbilt · FAO Schwarz</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">8:00 AM</div>
        <div class="event-title">☕ BREAKFAST: Levain Bakery <span class="badge badge-local">UWS icon</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">The most famous cookies in New York — massive, crispy outside, warm and doughy inside. Get one for everyone and eat them walking or at the hotel. The kids will ask for these every morning after the first one. Columbus Ave, 5 min from hotel.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$5–7 per cookie · Budget $25–30</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">9:30 – 10:15 AM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🏛️ Grand Central Terminal <span class="badge badge-photo">📸 Photo stop</span> <span class="badge badge-free">Free</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">Take the subway from Columbus Circle (A or D line, 4 stops). Grand Central is not a tourist trap — it's genuinely one of the most beautiful buildings in America. The star-painted ceiling, the famous clock, the cathedral scale of the main concourse. The kids will go quiet when they walk in. 30 minutes is enough.</div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ 30–40 minutes</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 Free · Subway ~$2.90/person</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">10:30 AM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🦪 EARLY LUNCH: Grand Central Oyster Bar <span class="badge badge-iconic">Since 1913</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">Right inside Grand Central — one of the oldest restaurants in the city, open since 1913. Vaulted tile ceilings, a long marble counter, the best chowder in Manhattan. Order oysters, chowder, and whatever's fresh. The kids can have chowder and fish — the menu has options. This is the kind of place that makes you feel like you're inside New York history.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$90–120 family · Reserve via OpenTable</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">12:30 – 2:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🌆 SUMMIT One Vanderbilt <span class="badge badge-reserve">⭐ Book ahead</span> <span class="badge badge-photo">📸 Photo stop</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">
          <strong>The best observatory experience in NYC for kids.</strong> Not just a view — a full immersive art experience: floor-to-ceiling mirror rooms, glass platforms where you appear to float 1,063 feet above Madison Avenue, a silver balloon room. Kids aged 6–7 think it's actual magic.<br><br>
          Friday morning slot is less crowded than weekends and cheaper. Skip the "Ascent" glass elevator upgrade — not necessary with young kids.
        </div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ 1.5–2 hours</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$44–50/adult · ~$33–38/child · Total family ~$155–175</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">3:00 – 4:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🪩 FAO Schwarz <span class="badge badge-kids">Kids highlight</span> <span class="badge badge-iconic">Legendary toy store</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">
          Walk from SUMMIT to 30 Rockefeller Plaza. FAO Schwarz is not just a toy store — it's a destination. The floor piano where Tom Hanks danced in <em>Big</em>. Toy soldiers at the entrance. A curated Hot Wheels section. A LEGO wall. Your kids will remember this.<br><br>
          You can browse everything without buying — but budget $50–100 if you want. The LEGO NYC exclusive sets (Brooklyn Bridge, Empire State) can't be found in Puerto Rico.
        </div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ 1.5 hours</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 Free to enter · Shopping at your discretion</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event tip">
        <div class="event-title">💡 Times Square — the right way</div>
        <div class="event-desc">You'll pass near Times Square heading back. If anyone wants to see it, do it from an Uber on the way home — the screens and lights through the window are just as impressive without the chaos. One drive-through is the perfect dose for this age group.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">7:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🍝 DINNER: Carmine's Italian <span class="badge badge-iconic">Family style since 1990</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">Legendary family-style Italian. Portions are enormous — one pasta feeds the whole table. The room is loud, which is perfect with kids. On 91st St near Broadway, close to the hotel. Locals celebrate here, not tourists. Reserve for 4.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$80–100 family · Reserve via OpenTable</div>
      </div>
    </div>
