  <!-- DAY 4 -->
  <div class="day-block">
    <div class="day-header">
      <div class="day-badge" style="background:var(--day4);"><span>Day</span>4</div>
      <div>
        <div class="day-title">Liberty, Brooklyn, Art &amp; The Mussels</div>
        <div class="day-zone">📍 Saturday Jun 13 · Battery Park · DUMBO · Brooklyn Bridge · Chelsea · West Village</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">7:30 AM</div>
        <div class="event-title">☕ BREAKFAST: Quick hotel or nearby deli</div>
        <div class="event-desc">Early start today — Saturday ferry crowds build fast. Keep breakfast simple and get moving. You'll make up for it at dinner.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$20–35</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">9:00 AM – 12:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🗽 Statue of Liberty + Ellis Island <span class="badge badge-reserve">⭐ Book NOW</span> <span class="badge badge-kids">Kids highlight</span> <span class="badge badge-photo">📸 The NYC moment</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">
          Uber to Battery Park for the first ferry. Saturday is the busiest day — book the 8 or 9 AM departure well in advance.<br><br>
          <strong>Ticket recommendation:</strong> Pedestal Access (included in the standard reserve ticket) is enough — the view from the pedestal is extraordinary and avoids 354 steps with kids. Crown tickets sell out months ahead anyway.<br><br>
          <strong>The moment that matters:</strong> When the Statue first emerges from the ferry. Watch your kids' faces. That's the memory.
        </div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ ~3 hours total</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$24 adults / $14 kids · Total ~$95–110 · Book at nps.gov/stli</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">1:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🍕 LUNCH: Grimaldi's Pizza, DUMBO <span class="badge badge-iconic">Coal-fired, legendary</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">Take the NYC Ferry from Pier 11 (Wall Street) to DUMBO ($4/person — a beautiful ride). Grimaldi's is a 3-minute walk from the DUMBO ferry stop. Coal-fired oven pizza, classic NYC pies. Arrive by 1 PM before the Saturday line gets long.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$50–65 family · NYC Ferry: $4/person</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">2:30 – 4:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🌉 DUMBO + Brooklyn Bridge <span class="badge badge-photo">📸 The NYC photo</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">
          You're already in DUMBO — the most photogenic neighborhood in Brooklyn.<br><br>
          <strong>The shot:</strong> Stand on Washington Street between Front and Water St. The Manhattan Bridge perfectly frames the end of the street. This is the most copied photo in NYC. Take it.<br><br>
          Then walk the Brooklyn Bridge toward Manhattan — 20 minutes across, skyline behind you the whole way. Go halfway, take the photos, and walk back or cross to Manhattan. The kids can absolutely do this walk.
        </div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ 2 hours</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 Free</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">5:00 – 6:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🎨 Artists &amp; Fleas at Chelsea Market <span class="badge badge-local">Local art · fair prices</span> <span class="badge badge-photo">📸 Photo stop</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">
          Uber from DUMBO to Chelsea Market (~20 min). Artists &amp; Fleas is a curated indoor marketplace of local NYC artists and makers inside Chelsea Market — prints, paintings, jewelry, ceramics, handmade goods. This is where you buy original art at real prices, not gallery markups.<br><br>
          <strong>What to look for:</strong> Original art prints by local artists ($25–$150), watercolors and small paintings ($50–$300), photography prints of NYC ($30–$100). Talk to the artists — they love it and will tell you the story behind the work.<br><br>
          <strong>Tip:</strong> The lineup rotates weekly so whatever you find is that week's selection. Arrive with an open mind, not a shopping list. The kids can browse too — there's always something that catches their eye.<br><br>
          After browsing, walk the High Line (elevated park above the market) for 20 minutes before dinner — it's steps away and the West Village views at golden hour are beautiful.
        </div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ 1.5 hours · Open daily 11 AM – 7 PM</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 Free to enter · Art from ~$25–$300 · Budget what you're comfortable with</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event mussel eat">
        <div class="event-time">7:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🦪 DINNER: Flex Mussels, West Village <span class="badge badge-mussel">🦪 MUSSEL NIGHT</span> <span class="badge badge-local">NYC's best mussels</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">
          <strong>This is your mussel dinner.</strong> Flex Mussels imports directly from Prince Edward Island and serves them in 23 globally-inspired preparations. The <strong>Fra Diavolo</strong> (spicy tomato) and the <strong>Parma</strong> (parmigiano cream, lemon, toasted garlic, crispy shallots) are the standouts. The broth soaked up with bread is the entire point.<br><br>
          Genuinely family-friendly — kids eat here regularly. Small room, warm atmosphere, serious mussels. Chelsea Market is a 5-minute walk from Flex Mussels — perfect flow after the gallery visit.<br><br>
          <strong>Reserve well ahead</strong> — small room, Saturday nights fill fast. Ask for the ground floor.
        </div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$90–120 family · Reserve via OpenTable or Resy</div>
      </div>
    </div>
