      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">11:00 AM – 1:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🏗️ Hudson Yards + The Vessel <span class="badge badge-photo">📸 Photo stop</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">
          NYC's most modern neighborhood. <strong>The Vessel</strong> — a 154-staircase spiral structure unlike anything else on earth — is free to climb but requires online registration in advance.<br><br>
          The mall has a LEGO Store and toy shops for any last-minute souvenirs. Keep it focused — you're heading to the airport this afternoon.
        </div>
        <div class="event-duration">⏱️ 2 hours</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 Vessel free · Shopping at your discretion</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event eat">
        <div class="event-time">1:00 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🥘 LUNCH: Mercado Little Spain, Hudson Yards <span class="badge badge-kids">Great for kids</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">José Andrés's Spanish food market — one of the best food experiences in NYC. Jamón, tapas, churros, paella, bocadillos. The kids will love the variety and the churros are non-negotiable. You'll feel right at home. The perfect last meal before flying back to Puerto Rico.</div>
        <div class="event-cost">💰 ~$55–75 family</div>
      </div>
      <div class="event attraction">
        <div class="event-time">3:00 – 4:30 PM</div>
        <div class="event-title">🌳 Central Park farewell — Alice in Wonderland <span class="badge badge-kids">Perfect ending</span></div>
        <div class="event-desc">One last Central Park stop before the airport. The <strong>Alice in Wonderland statue</strong> — kids from around the world climb on Alice, the Mad Hatter, the Cheshire Cat. A magical photo. Rent a rowboat on <strong>The Lake</strong> for 30 minutes if there's time. A quiet, beautiful close to the trip.</div>
