<div id="tips" class="section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <h2>Pro Tips</h2>
    <p>What only people who've done NYC with young kids know · Mistakes to avoid</p>
  </div>
  <div class="info-grid">
    <div class="info-card" style="border-top-color:var(--gold);">
      <h3>🎒 Pace &amp; logistics</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="icon">⏰</span> <strong>Eat early, move early:</strong> Lunch at 12 PM when places open. The 1–2 PM rush doubles wait times.</li>
        <li><span class="icon">🌡️</span> June in NYC hits 88–92°F. Carry water in thermoses from the hotel every day.</li>
        <li><span class="icon">🎒</span> Pack snacks in the bag — quick food options on the street are expensive.</li>
        <li><span class="icon">👟</span> Proper walking shoes for the kids, not sandals. Active days mean 4–6 miles on foot.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card" style="border-top-color:var(--rust);">
      <h3>🚫 Classic mistakes</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="icon">❌</span> <strong>6+ activities in one day.</strong> With ages 6–7, 2–3 is the real ceiling.</li>
        <li><span class="icon">❌</span> <strong>Times Square on foot at night.</strong> Extreme crowds, aggressive vendors, sensory overload for kids.</li>
        <li><span class="icon">❌</span> <strong>Missing the Washington St DUMBO photo.</strong> It's the most iconic NYC shot you'll ever take.</li>
        <li><span class="icon">❌</span> Not booking Liberty tickets early. Saturday summer ferries sell out weeks ahead.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card" style="border-top-color:var(--sage);">
      <h3>🚇 Smart transport</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="icon">🚇</span> Subway is safe and fast. Lines A/C/D from Columbus Circle cover 80% of Manhattan. Load a MetroCard or use a contactless card.</li>
        <li><span class="icon">🚕</span> Uber XL for airport runs and when the kids are exhausted.</li>
        <li><span class="icon">⛴️</span> NYC Ferry ($4/person) to Brooklyn — scenic, cheap, the kids love it.</li>
        <li><span class="icon">🚶</span> Your hotel zone is the most walkable in NYC. Hotel → AMNH → Central Park all on foot.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card" style="border-top-color:var(--day5);">
